topic: Sport Workflow Series ("Association Football Players explorative search")

goals.1: Identify the BGP for association football player
goals.2: Identify the BGP for association football club
goals.3: Identify the BGP for association football league
goals.4: Return for each european country the number of association football leagues (the result set must be a list of triples country IRI, label and #leagues).
goals.5: Identify the BGP for the ballon d'Or award
goals.6: Return the countries which have at least two different players of their nationality (consider the country of citizenship) who won the ballon d'Or (the result set must be a list of triples country IRI, label and #different players).
goals.7: Identify the BGP of the FIFA World Cup
goals.8: Who are the players who partecipated in more than 4 world's cup editions? (the result set must be a list of triples player IRI, label and #participations).
goals.9: Consider the countries that won the FIFA World Cup at least twice. Find the players of those countries won the ballon d'Or (the result set must be a list of couples player IRI and label).

1.narrative: I search for the propreties that has Cristiano Ronaldo
1.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?name WHERE { wd:Q11571 ?p ?obj . ?p sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 200

1.narrative: To find the BPG for association football player, I take a look to the occupation of Cristiano ronaldo.
1.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?Occupation ?OccupationName WHERE { wd:Q11571 ?p ?obj. ?obj wdt:P106 ?Occupation. ?Occupation sc:name ?OccupationName. } LIMIT 200

1.narrative: The final query for this task it's the same as the last query.
1.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?Occupation ?OccupationName WHERE { wd:Q11571 ?p ?obj. ?obj wdt:P106 ?Occupation. ?Occupation sc:name ?OccupationName. } LIMIT 200

4.narrative: We get all instance from association football leagues, that is going to give me all the leagues of the world.
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?footballleague ?footballleagueName WHERE { ?footballleague wdt:P31 wd:Q15991303 . ?footballleague sc:name ?footballleagueName . } LIMIT 3

4.narrative: Now we explore the properties that a league has searching for the propertie country.
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?name WHERE { wd:Q304228 ?p ?obj . ?p sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 100

4.narrative: Now we add to the previus query the country of each league.
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?footballleague ?footballleagueName ?countryleagueName WHERE { ?footballleague wdt:P31 wd:Q15991303 . ?footballleague wdt:P17 ?countryleague . ?footballleague sc:name ?footballleagueName . ?countryleague sc:name ?countryleagueName. } ORDER BY ASC (?countryleagueName) LIMIT 10

4.narrative: Now we only show the countries and how many leagues each country have.
4.query: SELECT ?countryleagueName (COUNT(*) AS ?total) WHERE { ?footballleague wdt:P31 wd:Q15991303 . ?footballleague wdt:P17 ?countryleague . ?countryleague sc:name ?countryleagueName. } GROUP BY ?countryleagueName ORDER BY ASC (?countryleagueName) LIMIT 10

4.narrative: Now we filter the coutries to only the european ones.
4.query: SELECT ?country ?countryName (COUNT(*) AS ?numberofLeagues) WHERE { ?footballleague wdt:P31 wd:Q15991303 . ?footballleague wdt:P17 ?country . ?country wdt:P30 wd:Q46 . ?country sc:name ?countryName. } ORDER BY ASC (?countryName) LIMIT 100

6.narrative:
I'm going to start finding all the persons that are football players
I take advantage of the previous queries and use the properties P106(Ocupation) and the value Q937857 (association football player)
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?footballplayers ?footballplayersName WHERE { ?footballplayers wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?footballplayers wdt:P106 wd:Q937857 . ?footballplayers sc:name ?footballplayersName . } LIMIT 20

6.narrative:
I use the previous query and add those football players that won the ballon d'ore.
I take the value of ballon d'ore from the task 5. Q166177
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?footballplayers ?footballplayersName WHERE { ?footballplayers wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?footballplayers wdt:P106 wd:Q937857 . ?footballplayers wdt:P166 wd:Q166177 . ?footballplayers sc:name ?footballplayersName . } LIMIT 100

6.narrative:
Now I add the country of each player.
We take the property of country from the properties that has Cristiano Ronaldo.  P27
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?futballplayers ?footballplayersName ?countryName WHERE { ?footballplayers wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?footballplayers wdt:P106 wd:Q937857 . ?footballplayers wdt:P166 wd:Q166177 . ?footballplayers wdt:P27 ?country . ?footballplayers sc:name ?footballplayersName . ?country sc:name ?countryName . } ORDER BY ASC (?countryName) LIMIT 100

6.narrative: Now I only show the countries
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?country ?countryName WHERE { ?footballplayers wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?footballplayers wdt:P106 wd:Q937857 . ?footballplayers wdt:P166 wd:Q166177 . ?footballplayers wdt:P27 ?country . ?country sc:name ?countryName . } ORDER BY ASC (?countryName) LIMIT 100

6.narrative: Now I try to count the winners for each country and show the number.
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?country ?countryName (COUNT(*) AS ?winners) WHERE { ?footballplayers wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?footballplayers wdt:P106 wd:Q937857 . ?footballplayers wdt:P166 wd:Q166177 . ?footballplayers wdt:P27 ?country . ?country sc:name ?countryName . } ORDER BY ASC (?countryName) LIMIT 100

6.narrative: Now I filter to only show the countries with more than 2 players that won the ballon d'or
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?country ?countryName (COUNT(*) AS ?winners) WHERE { ?footballplayers wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?footballplayers wdt:P106 wd:Q937857 . ?footballplayers wdt:P166 wd:Q166177 . ?footballplayers wdt:P27 ?country . ?country sc:name ?countryName . FILTER (?winners >2) } ORDER BY ASC (?countryName) LIMIT 100

6.narrative:
write your final query
Now I filter to only show the countries with more than 2 players that won the ballon d'or
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?country ?countryName (COUNT(*) AS ?winners) WHERE { ?footballplayers wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?footballplayers wdt:P106 wd:Q937857 . ?footballplayers wdt:P166 wd:Q166177 . ?footballplayers wdt:P27 ?country . ?country sc:name ?countryName . } GROUP BY ?country ?countryName HAVING (count(*) >= 2) ORDER BY ASC (?countryName) LIMIT 100

SELECT DISTINCT ?footballplayers ?footballplayersName WHERE { ?footballplayers wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?footballplayers wdt:P106 wd:Q937857 . ?footballplayers wdt:P166 wd:Q166177 . ?footballplayers wdt:P27 ?country . { SELECT DISTINCT ?country (COUNT(*) AS ?Times) WHERE { ?allworldcups wdt:P3450 wd:Q19317 . ?allworldcups wdt:P1346 ?winner . ?winner wdt:P17 ?country . } GROUP BY ?country HAVING (count(*) >=2) ORDER BY ?country } ?footballplayers sc:name ?footballplayersName . } ORDER BY ASC (?footballplayersName) LIMIT 100

7.narrative: Lets see from whom it's instance of

7.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?oName WHERE { wd:Q37285 wdt:P3450 ?obj . ?obj sc:name ?oName. } LIMIT 100

7.narrative: I get the same query that in the task 6 to get all the players.
7.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?footballplayers ?footballplayersName WHERE { ?footballplayers wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?footballplayers wdt:P106 wd:Q937857 . ?footballplayers sc:name ?footballplayersName . } LIMIT 3

7.narrative: Now I am gonna explore all the tournaments that the players participated.
7.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?footballplayers ?footballplayersName ?participatedName WHERE { ?footballplayers wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?footballplayers wdt:P106 wd:Q937857 . ?footballplayers wdt:P1344 ?participated . ?footballplayers sc:name ?footballplayersName . ?participated sc:name ?participatedName . } ORDER BY ?footballplayersName LIMIT 3

7.narrative: Now I am going to filter the variable ?participated to get only the players that participated on a Fifa world cup
7.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?footballplayers ?footballplayersName ?participatedName WHERE { ?footballplayers wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?footballplayers wdt:P106 wd:Q937857 . ?footballplayers wdt:P1344 ?participated . ?participated wdt:P3450 wd:Q19317. ?footballplayers sc:name ?footballplayersName . ?participated sc:name ?participatedName . } GROUP BY ?footballplayers ORDER BY ?footballplayersName LIMIT 30

7.narrative: Now I tried to count the times each player appears.
7.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?footballplayers ?footballplayersName (COUNT(*) AS ?Times) WHERE { ?footballplayers wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?footballplayers wdt:P106 wd:Q937857 . ?footballplayers wdt:P1344 ?participated . ?participated wdt:P3450 wd:Q19317. ?footballplayers sc:name ?footballplayersName . ?participated sc:name ?participatedName . } GROUP BY ?footballplayers ?footballplayersName ORDER BY DESC (?Times) LIMIT 100

7.narrative: Now I add a filter to show only the players that have been in more than 4 world cups.
7.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?footballplayers ?footballplayersName (COUNT(*) AS ?Times) WHERE { ?footballplayers wdt:P31 wd:Q5 . ?footballplayers wdt:P106 wd:Q937857 . ?footballplayers wdt:P1344 ?participated . ?participated wdt:P3450 wd:Q19317. ?footballplayers sc:name ?footballplayersName . ?participated sc:name ?participatedName . } GROUP BY ?footballplayers ?footballplayersName HAVING (COUNT(*) >4 ) ORDER BY DESC (?Times) LIMIT 30

9.narrative: I remember the property sports season of league or competition(P345O) from previous tasks and I try to show all the world cups
9.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?allworldcups ?allworldcupsName WHERE { ?allworldcups wdt:P3450 wd:Q19317 . ?allworldcups sc:name ?allworldcupsName . } ORDER BY ?allworldcupsName LIMIT 100

9.narrative:
Now that I have all the World cups, I try to get the country that won each one of them. From last queries I know the property winner(P1346) lets get
the winners
9.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?allworldcups ?allworldcupsName ?winner ?winnerName WHERE { ?allworldcups wdt:P3450 wd:Q19317 . ?allworldcups wdt:P1346 ?winner . ?allworldcups sc:name ?allworldcupsName . ?winner sc:name ?winnerName . } ORDER BY ?allworldcupsName LIMIT 100

9.narrative:
With last query I get the teams of the countries but not the country itself, so I am going to explore the properties of one team.
This case the properties of Uruguay Team (Q134916).
9.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?name WHERE { wd:Q134916 ?p ?obj . ?p sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 200

9.narrative: With the last query, I get the country property (P17) that I am gonna use to get the countries instead of the teams.
9.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?allworldcups ?worldcupName ?countryWinner WHERE { ?allworldcups wdt:P3450 wd:Q19317 . ?allworldcups wdt:P1346 ?winner . ?winner wdt:P17 ?country . ?allworldcups sc:name ?worldcupName . ?country sc:name ?countryWinner . } ORDER BY ?allworldcupsName LIMIT 100

9.narrative: Now I only get the countries and count the times that each country won the world cup.
9.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?countryWinner (COUNT(*) AS ?Times) WHERE { ?allworldcups wdt:P3450 wd:Q19317 . ?allworldcups wdt:P1346 ?winner . ?winner wdt:P17 ?country . ?country sc:name ?countryWinner . } GROUP BY ?countryWinner ORDER BY ?countryWinner LIMIT 100

9.narrative: Now I only get the ones that won at least two times.
9.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?countryWinner (COUNT(*) AS ?Times) WHERE { ?allworldcups wdt:P3450 wd:Q19317 . ?allworldcups wdt:P1346 ?winner . ?winner wdt:P17 ?country . ?country sc:name ?countryWinner . } GROUP BY ?countryWinner HAVING (count(*) >=2) ORDER BY ?countryWinner LIMIT 100
